,Recommended,292780,33063023,Posted: 30 June,all,Neptunella,"Unlike with Freddi Fish, which was my favourite franchise as a kid, I've first encountered Pajama Sam not long ago and was immediately charmed by its great art and the very idea of a young kid who travels through the worlds of his imagination, always based on the most recent events in his life. After playing the games I can only say - what a shame that I didn't have them as a kid! I'm positive I would fall in love with them, because they have everything you want from a kids' game - a good message, funny and memorable characters (especially Sam who's just the cutest kid ever), an environment you can interact with, minigames and, surprisingly, very smart sense of humour. If you have children, I stongly recommend that you play Pajama Sam series with them, and if not - just try it yourself, it may very well return you to your own childhood. It sure did that for me."
